.TH E2FSCK 8
.SH NAME
e2fsck, fsck.ext2 \- check and repair an ELKS-compatible ext2 filesystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B e2fsck
[\-apnyfv]
.I device
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.I e2fsck
checks the ELKS ext2 subset: ext2 revision 0, 1K blocks, and no optional
features.
It repairs metadata used by the ELKS kernel: inode and block bitmaps,
free counts, link counts, dead inodes, invalid block pointers, and basic
directory entry sanity.
.TP 5
.B \-a
Automatically repair detected problems.
.TP 5
.B \-p
Preen mode. This is the same as
.BR \-a .
.TP 5
.B \-y
Answer yes to all repairs. This is the same as
.BR \-a .
.TP 5
.B \-n
Never modify the filesystem.
.TP 5
.B \-f
Force a full check even if the filesystem is marked clean.
.TP 5
.B \-v
Print a short summary.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP 24
.B e2fsck \-f /dev/hdb1
# Force a full ext2 metadata check
.TP 24
.B e2fsck \-p /dev/hdb1
# Automatically repair a dirty ext2 filesystem
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR mkfs.ext2 (8),
.BR fsck (8),
.BR mount (8).
